Reasoning: The paper deals with the design and performance analysis of a communication system based on OFDM with unique word prefix and complex number Reed-Solomon coding. This topic falls under the broad area of information theory and communication systems, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with the fundamental limits of communication and coding. cs.COMM (Communications) is also a likely category as it deals with the design and analysis of communication systems. cs.SI (Signal Processing) is another possible category as it deals with the processing of signals in communication systems. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are less likely categories, but they may still be relevant as the paper deals with the design and optimization of a communication system.
